Tic Tac Toe Game

This project implements a simple Tic Tac Toe game with features like saving game state, retrieving game state, and live collaboration using Socket.io. The game is built using Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, and Socket.io on the backend, and React on the frontend.

Table of Contents

- Features
- Prerequisites
- Getting Started
- Installation
- Usage
- Contributing

Features

- Allows a single player to play the Tic Tac Toe game.
- Saves and retrieves game state using MongoDB.
- Implements live collaboration using Socket.io, enabling multiple users to play the game simultaneously.

Prerequisites

- Node.js (v14.x or higher)
- MongoDB (v4.x or higher)
- npm or yarn

Getting Started

To get started with this project, follow the steps below.

Installation

1. Clone the repository to your local machine.

bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/tic-tac-toe.git
cd tic-tac-toe


2. Install the required dependencies for both the server and the client.

bash
# Install server dependencies
cd server
npm install

# Install client dependencies
cd ../client
npm install

Usage

Start the Server

1. Navigate to the server directory.

#bash
cd server


2. Start the server.

#bash
npm start


The server will start on http://localhost:5000 by default.

Start the Client

1. Navigate to the client directory.

#bash
cd client


2. Start the React application.

#bash
npm start


The React app will start on http://localhost:3000 by default.

Now you can access the Tic Tac Toe game through your browser.

